Fixed errors when creating extremely long cables.
Fixed the `trace_paths` management command (run by `nautobot-server post_upgrade`) not regenerating missing breakout cable fan-out lane paths.
Fixed the `trace_paths` management command aborting partway through when it encountered inconsistent existing cable data (such as a cabling loop); it now skips the affected origin and continues.
Fixed corrupted connection tables (in both the cable detail view and the HTMX connection-edit form) for breakout cables with a meshed connector mapping, such as a polarity-shuffled 2x2.
Fixed missing validation that allowed a multi-connector (breakout) cable type to be attached to termination types that don't support breakout (such as console or power terminations).
Fixed the cable edit form disallowing all cable types for cables with non-breakout-eligible terminations; single-connector cable types are now permitted.
